rComments: Awesome professor - who gives fun lectures every time, calls for class participations as well discussion from students often, and even Timbits once in class.
Prof. Korteweg is a great prof. She's very bright and approachable. She's also passionate about her research.

This professor is judgemental, if she has a bad/good preception of u it will have an affect on ur grades.  Participation is mandatory in class in order to do well.  She is not organized with her lectures, & mixes her materials all over the place, but expects u to be organized.  She is also unclear about her expectation so it's hard for u to do well

I agree: She is unclear with her instructions and what she wants.  Her lecturing is also pretty scattered, and she's too attached to her notes when trying to teach concepts.  Will often read straight off the page using "big words". Not bad overall though.
This professor is very enthusiatic about her classes, however, she is extremely particular and is unclear with instructions.

This prof is very approachable and friendly, however, she is undeniably an inexperienced professor. She is scattered when she lectures and is attached to her power point slides, leading you to have to rely on writing down what she says, rather than learning the material during lectures. Her grading is unfair and lower than most professors.

By far one of the best profs I have ever had.  Clear and concise lectures, she seems genuinely interested in students' success.  She doesn't have the "I am professor and therefore better than you" attitude that most profs have,which is refreshing!!  Lots of assignments = lots of work, but on the plus side no exams.
